My first clue was that `@Transactional`/AOP probably uses different types of proxies, so I&#39;ve also inspected the reference to `MyTransactionalService`. Inside of a method of the service `this` points to instance of basic `MyTransactionalService`, but outside of the class DI container will inject a reference to `MyTransactionalService$$SpringCGLIB$$0`.

So, it looks like the same CGLIB approach is used for both cases: `MyConfigClass` and `MyTransactionalService`. But why methods of `MyConfigClass` see proxied object behind `this` ref, and at the same time methods of `MyTransactionalService` see bare non-proxied object?

